FBIS3-6104 "dreas050_c_94005" FBIS-EAS-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Mar 1994 North Korea 11 Mar U.S.-ROK `War Exercise' Reported SK1303083994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0809 GMT 13 Mar 94 SK1303083994 Pyongyang KCNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Pyongyang, March 13 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists on March 11 staged a war exercise targeted against the North in the sky above Kunwi, Yoju and Sangdong, South Korea, with the mobilisation of formations of Pacific-based assault planes and above 400 fighter-bombers, observation planes and reconnaissance planes belonging to the U.S. Air Force present in South Korea and the puppet Air Force, according to military sources. On the same day, armed bandits of the puppet Army in Yonchon County and Paju County, Kyonggi Province, and Chorwon County and Inje County, South Korean Kangwon Province, fired at random large-calibre machine gun and automatic rifles toward the Demilitarized Zone along the Military Demarcation Line, thus whipping up war hysterics.
